Theory
1. What is SPA (Single Page Application)?

A Single Page Application (SPA) is a web application that loads a single HTML page and dynamically updates the content without refreshing the entire page.

Benefits of SPA
Faster navigation
Better user experience
Reduced server load
Less bandwidth usage
Smooth page transitions
2. What is React?

React is an open-source JavaScript library developed by Facebook for building user interfaces, especially single-page applications.

It allows developers to create reusable UI components and efficiently update the webpage whenever data changes.

3. Working of React
User performs an action.
State or data changes.
React creates a new Virtual DOM.
React compares it with the previous Virtual DOM.
Only the changed elements are updated in the Real DOM.
The browser displays the updated UI.
4. Difference between SPA and MPA
SPA	MPA
Loads one HTML page	Loads multiple HTML pages
Faster navigation	Slower navigation
No full page reload	Reloads every page
Better user experience	Traditional user experience
Uses JavaScript heavily	More server-side rendering
5. Pros and Cons of SPA
Advantages
Fast loading
Better performance
Easy API integration
Smooth user experience
Reusable components
Disadvantages
Initial loading may be slow
SEO is difficult without SSR
JavaScript dependency
Browser history management is complex
6. Virtual DOM

Virtual DOM is a lightweight copy of the Real DOM maintained by React.

Instead of updating the complete webpage, React compares the old Virtual DOM with the new Virtual DOM and updates only the changed parts.

Advantages
Faster rendering
Better performance
Efficient DOM updates
7. Features of React
Component-based architecture
Virtual DOM
JSX support
